---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "@/components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";

const cards = [
  {
    title: "Registry",
    description: "Official public registry for agent service discovery. Find and list services that support Agent Auth.",
    href: "/registry",
    label: "Browse registry",
  },
  {
    title: "Implementations",
    description: "Libraries, SDKs, and server implementations of Agent Auth across languages and frameworks.",
    href: "/implementations",
    label: "View implementations",
  },
  {
    title: "Examples",
    description: "Real integration patterns — from basic registration to multi-step approval flows and capability escalation.",
    href: "/examples",
    label: "View examples",
  },
  {
    title: "Community",
    description: "Join the discussion — ask questions, share implementations, and help shape the protocol.",
    href: "https://github.com/AgentAuthProtocol/agent-auth-protocol/discussions",
    label: "Join the community",
    external: true,
  },
];
---

<Layout title="Agent Auth Protocol — AI Agent Identity & Authorization" darkMode={true}>
  <Nav active="/" showThemeToggle={true} />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none select-none" aria-hidden="true" style="background: radial-gradient(ellipse 80% 60% at 50% 40%, var(--color-fg), transparent); opacity: 0.03;"></div>
    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-[1400px] px-5 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24">
      <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-10 lg:gap-12 xl:gap-16">
        <!-- Left: copy + FAQ -->
        <div class="lg:flex-1 lg:pt-8">
          <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-[3.25rem] tracking-tight leading-[1.1] mb-6">
            <span class="font-semibold">Agent Auth</span> <span class="font-light">Protocol</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed max-w-lg mb-8">
            An implementation-oriented protocol that gives AI agents their own identity, permissions, and lifecycle, so services can authenticate, authorize, and audit them independently.
          </p>
          <div class="mb-10"></div>
          <div class="border border-dashed border-[var(--color-border)] max-w-lg">
            <details name="faq" class="group border-b border-dashed border-[var(--color-border)] last:border-b-0">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-4 py-3 cursor-pointer select-none">
                <span class="text-[13px] font-medium">Why does this need to exist?</span>
                <span class="text-[var(--color-muted)] text-xs font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] ml-3 shrink-0 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform">+</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="faq-content"><div><div class="px-4 pb-3 text-[12px] text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-[1.8]">Today, agents borrow a user's OAuth token or a shared client credential. That collapses the agent into someone else's identity — the server can't tell which agent made a request, can't scope permissions per agent, and can't revoke one without revoking all of them. Agent Auth gives each agent its own cryptographic identity, its own granted capabilities, and its own lifecycle — so services can authenticate, scope, and revoke each one independently.</div></div></div>
            </details>
            <details name="faq" class="group border-b border-dashed border-[var(--color-border)] last:border-b-0">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-4 py-3 cursor-pointer select-none">
                <span class="text-[13px] font-medium">How does it work?</span>
                <span class="text-[var(--color-muted)] text-xs font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] ml-3 shrink-0 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform">+</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="faq-content"><div><div class="px-4 pb-3 text-[12px] text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-[1.8]">An agent registers with a server and gets its own keypair and identity. The user approves what the agent can do via a device authorization flow — similar to linking a TV app. Once approved, the agent signs a short-lived JWT for every request it makes. The server verifies the signature, checks the agent's permissions, and processes the call. Every request traces back to a specific agent.</div></div></div>
            </details>
            <details name="faq" class="group border-b border-dashed border-[var(--color-border)] last:border-b-0">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-4 py-3 cursor-pointer select-none">
                <span class="text-[13px] font-medium">How is this different from MCP or OAuth?</span>
                <span class="text-[var(--color-muted)] text-xs font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] ml-3 shrink-0 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform">+</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="faq-content"><div><div class="px-4 pb-3 text-[12px] text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-[1.8]">MCP defines how agents talk to tools. OAuth defines how users authorize apps. Neither models the agent itself as an identity. With MCP alone, agents use the user's tokens — there's no per-agent audit trail, scoping, or revocation. Agent Auth adds the missing layer: it treats the runtime agent as a first-class principal sitting between the user and the service. You can use all three together.</div></div></div>
            </details>
            <details name="faq" class="group">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-4 py-3 cursor-pointer select-none">
                <span class="text-[13px] font-medium">Is this tied to Better Auth?</span>
                <span class="text-[var(--color-muted)] text-xs font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] ml-3 shrink-0 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform">+</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="faq-content"><div><div class="px-4 pb-3 text-[12px] text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-[1.8]">Agent Auth is an open protocol — Ed25519 keypairs, device authorization, signed JWTs. Better Auth ships the reference implementation that handles everything out of the box, but the protocol is designed to be implementable in any language or framework.</div></div></div>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right: interactive demo — fixed height, no layout shift -->
        <div class="lg:w-[520px] xl:w-[560px] shrink-0 w-full lg:pt-[2rem] relative">
          <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)] overflow-hidden" id="hero-demo">
            <!-- Prompt area with typing -->
            <div class="px-4 py-3 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
                <span class="text-[var(--color-muted)] text-[13px] mt-px select-none shrink-0">›</span>
                <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
                  <span class="text-[13px] leading-snug" id="demo-prompt"></span><span id="demo-cursor" class="inline-block w-[1.5px] h-[15px] bg-[var(--color-fg)] align-middle ml-px" style="animation: blink 1s step-end infinite;"></span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Timeline — fixed height, content scrolls within -->
            <div class="h-[370px] overflow-hidden relative" id="demo-timeline">
              <div class="px-4 py-2 h-full overflow-y-auto" id="demo-scroll">
                <div id="demo-steps"></div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Footer: replay / next -->
            <div id="demo-footer" class="border-t border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2 flex items-center justify-center" style="visibility:hidden;">
              <button id="demo-replay-btn" class="text-[10px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] hover:text-[var(--color-fg)] transition-colors cursor-pointer">↻ Replay</button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cards -->
  <section class="relative">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1400px] px-5 sm:px-6 pb-20">
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-px bg-[var(--color-border)] border border-[var(--color-border)]">
        {cards.map((card) => (
          <a
            href={card.href}
            target={card.external ? "_blank" : undefined}
            rel={card.external ? "noopener noreferrer" : undefined}
            class="group bg-[var(--color-bg)] p-5 flex flex-col gap-3 hover:bg-[var(--color-surface)] transition-colors"
          >
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
              <h3 class="text-[13px] font-semibold">{card.title}</h3>
              <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-[var(--color-muted)] opacity-0 -translate-x-1 group-hover:opacity-100 group-hover:translate-x-0 transition-all duration-200" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14"/><path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7"/></svg>
            </div>
            <p class="text-[12px] leading-[1.7] text-[var(--color-muted)] flex-1">{card.description}</p>
            <span class="text-[10px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] group-hover:text-[var(--color-fg)] transition-colors flex items-center gap-1.5">
              {card.label}
              {card.external && (
                <svg class="w-2.5 h-2.5 opacity-40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6"/><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"/><line x1="10" y1="14" x2="21" y2="3"/></svg>
              )}
            </span>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Ask trigger — iOS home indicator style -->
  <div class="fixed bottom-0 left-1/2 z-40 flex flex-col items-center" id="ask-trigger-wrap" style="translate: -50% 100%; opacity: 0; transition: translate .5s cubic-bezier(.32,.72,0,1), opacity .4s ease;">
    <button
      id="ask-trigger"
      class="flex flex-col items-center gap-2.5 cursor-pointer group px-6 pt-3 pb-5 backdrop-blur-md bg-[var(--color-bg)]/80 rounded-t-lg"
    >
      <span class="flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-[var(--color-muted)] group-hover:text-[var(--color-fg)] transition-colors" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <rect x="4" y="4" width="16" height="16" rx="4" class="ask-agent-body"/>
          <circle cx="9.5" cy="12" r="1.5" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" class="ask-agent-eye"/>
          <circle cx="14.5" cy="12" r="1.5" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" class="ask-agent-eye"/>
          <line x1="12" y1="1" x2="12" y2="4" class="ask-agent-antenna"/>
          <circle cx="12" cy="1" r="1" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" class="ask-agent-dot"/>
        </svg>
        <span class="text-[10px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-[color-mix(in_oklch,var(--color-fg)_55%,transparent)] group-hover:text-[var(--color-fg)] transition-colors">Learn about the protocol</span>
      </span>
      <span id="ask-wave" class="block w-10 h-[3px] rounded-full bg-[var(--color-fg)] opacity-80 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity"></span>
    </button>
  </div>

  <!-- Ask sheet (fullscreen overlay) -->
  <div id="ask-sheet" class="fixed inset-0 z-50">
    <div id="ask-backdrop" class="absolute inset-0 bg-[var(--color-bg)]"></div>
    <div id="ask-panel" class="absolute inset-0 flex flex-col">
      <!-- Sheet header -->
      <nav class="shrink-0 relative z-10 bg-[var(--color-bg)]">
        <div class="mx-auto flex items-center h-11 px-5 sm:px-6 max-w-[1400px]">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5">
            <span class="text-sm font-normal tracking-[0.08em] uppercase font-[family-name:var(--font-pixel)]">AGENT-AUTH</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ml-auto">
            <button id="ask-close" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] hover:text-[var(--color-fg)] transition-colors cursor-pointer">
              Close
              <kbd class="text-[9px] px-1 py-0.5 border border-[var(--color-border)] text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-none">ESC</kbd>
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="h-px" style="background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, var(--color-border) 15%, var(--color-border) 85%, transparent);"></div>
      </nav>

      <!-- Sheet body -->
      <div id="ask-response-area" class="flex-1 overflow-y-auto min-h-0">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[820px] w-full px-5 sm:px-8 py-8 sm:py-10">
          <div id="ask-welcome">
            <div class="mb-10">
              <p class="text-[11px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">Overview</p>
              <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight leading-[1.2] mb-5">What is Agent Auth Protocol?</h1>
              <div class="ask-prose">
                <p>Agent Auth is an open protocol that gives AI agents their own identity. Instead of borrowing a user's OAuth token or sharing a single API key, each agent gets its own cryptographic keypair, its own granted capabilities, and its own lifecycle.</p>
                <p>The core flow is simple: a <strong>host</strong> (like Cursor, an MCP server, or a CLI tool) registers an <strong>agent</strong> with a server. The agent authenticates using Ed25519-signed JWTs. The user approves capabilities through a device authorization flow — similar to logging into a streaming app on your TV.</p>
                <p>This means servers can see exactly which agent made a request, scope what each agent can do, and revoke one agent without affecting others. It works for both <strong>delegated</strong> agents (acting on behalf of a user) and <strong>autonomous</strong> agents (operating independently).</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="border-t border-[var(--color-border)] pt-8">
              <p class="text-[11px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">Dive deeper</p>
              <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-2">
                <button class="ask-chip text-left px-4 py-3 text-[13px] text-[var(--color-fg)] border border-[var(--color-border)] hover:bg-[var(--color-surface)] transition-colors cursor-pointer">How does agent registration work?</button>
                <button class="ask-chip text-left px-4 py-3 text-[13px] text-[var(--color-fg)] border border-[var(--color-border)] hover:bg-[var(--color-surface)] transition-colors cursor-pointer">Explain the device authorization flow</button>
                <button class="ask-chip text-left px-4 py-3 text-[13px] text-[var(--color-fg)] border border-[var(--color-border)] hover:bg-[var(--color-surface)] transition-colors cursor-pointer">Delegated vs autonomous agents</button>
                <button class="ask-chip text-left px-4 py-3 text-[13px] text-[var(--color-fg)] border border-[var(--color-border)] hover:bg-[var(--color-surface)] transition-colors cursor-pointer">What are capabilities?</button>
                <button class="ask-chip text-left px-4 py-3 text-[13px] text-[var(--color-fg)] border border-[var(--color-border)] hover:bg-[var(--color-surface)] transition-colors cursor-pointer sm:col-span-2">How do agents sign requests?</button>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="ask-messages" class="hidden"></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Sheet input -->
      <div class="shrink-0 relative z-10 bg-[var(--color-bg)]">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[820px] w-full px-5 sm:px-8 py-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 border border-[color-mix(in_oklch,var(--color-fg)_8%,transparent)] focus-within:border-[color-mix(in_oklch,var(--color-fg)_15%,transparent)] bg-[var(--color-surface)] transition-colors">
            <input
              id="ask-sheet-input"
              type="text"
              placeholder="Ask anything about the protocol…"
              autocomplete="off"
              class="flex-1 text-[14px] font-[family-name:var(--font-sans)] bg-transparent text-[var(--color-fg)] placeholder:text-[color-mix(in_oklch,var(--color-fg)_30%,transparent)] focus:outline-none min-w-0"
            />
            <button id="ask-send" class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[color-mix(in_oklch,var(--color-fg)_8%,transparent)] text-[var(--color-muted)] hover:bg-[color-mix(in_oklch,var(--color-fg)_15%,transparent)] hover:text-[var(--color-fg)] transition-all cursor-pointer disabled:opacity-20" disabled>
              <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 19V5"/><path d="m5 12 7-7 7 7"/></svg>
            </button>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[10px] text-[var(--color-muted)] text-center mt-2">AI-generated — verify important details</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style is:global>
    @keyframes blink { 0%,100%{opacity:1} 50%{opacity:0} }
    @keyframes spin { from{transform:rotate(0deg)} to{transform:rotate(360deg)} }

    details.group .faq-content {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-rows: 0fr;
      transition: grid-template-rows 0.25s ease;
    }
    details.group[open] .faq-content {
      grid-template-rows: 1fr;
    }
    details.group .faq-content > div {
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    @keyframes agent-blink {
      0%, 42%, 46%, 100% { scale: 1 1; }
      44% { scale: 1 0.1; }
    }
    .ask-agent-eye {
      transform-origin: center;
      animation: agent-blink 3s ease-in-out infinite;
      animation-delay: 1.8s;
    }
    @keyframes indicator-pulse {
      0%, 100% { opacity: 0.8; }
      50% { opacity: 1; }
    }
    #ask-wave {
      animation: indicator-pulse 2.5s ease-in-out infinite;
      animation-delay: 2s;
    }

    #ask-sheet {
      visibility: hidden;
      opacity: 0;
      transition: visibility 0s .25s, opacity .25s ease;
    }
    #ask-sheet.open {
      visibility: visible;
      opacity: 1;
      transition-delay: 0s;
    }

    .ask-prose {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.95;
      color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 78%, transparent);
    }
    .ask-prose > p:first-child {
      font-size: 17px;
      line-height: 1.85;
      color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 88%, transparent);
    }
    .ask-prose p { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .ask-prose p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .ask-prose strong { font-weight: 600; color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 90%, transparent); }
    .ask-prose a { text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; text-decoration-color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 20%, transparent); }
    .ask-prose a:hover { text-decoration-color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 55%, transparent); }
    .ask-prose code:not(pre code) {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.82em;
      padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
      background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 5%, transparent);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 85%, transparent);
    }
    .ask-prose pre {
      margin: 1.35rem 0;
      padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem;
      background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 3%, var(--color-bg));
      border: 1px solid color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 8%, transparent);
      border-radius: 10px;
      overflow-x: auto;
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 12.5px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 70%, transparent);
      box-shadow: inset 0 1px 0 color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 3%, transparent);
    }
    .ask-prose pre code { padding: 0; background: none; border: none; font-size: inherit; color: inherit; text-shadow: none; }
    .ask-prose pre code .token.comment,
    .ask-prose pre code .token.prolog,
    .ask-prose pre code .token.doctype { color: var(--color-muted); }
    .ask-prose pre code .token.punctuation { color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 50%, transparent); }
    .ask-prose pre code .token.property,
    .ask-prose pre code .token.tag,
    .ask-prose pre code .token.boolean,
    .ask-prose pre code .token.number,
    .ask-prose pre code .token.constant { color: #b5695a; }
    .ask-prose pre code .token.string,
    .ask-prose pre code .token.char,
    .ask-prose pre code .token.attr-value { color: #698a5b; }
    .ask-prose pre code .token.keyword,
    .ask-prose pre code .token.selector { color: #7c6ba5; }
    .ask-prose pre code .token.function { color: #5a8a8a; }
    .ask-prose pre code .token.operator { color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 60%, transparent); }
    .ask-prose ul, .ask-prose ol {
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .ask-prose ul { list-style: disc; }
    .ask-prose ol { list-style: decimal; }
    .ask-prose li { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
    .ask-prose li > p { margin-bottom: 0.35rem; }
    .ask-prose h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-top: 2.1rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
      color: var(--color-fg);
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }
    .ask-prose h3 {
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: 0.98rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-top: 1.6rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.55rem;
      color: var(--color-fg);
    }
    .ask-prose blockquote { border-left: 2px solid var(--color-border); padding-left: 1rem; margin: 1rem 0; color: var(--color-muted); font-style: italic; }
    .ask-prose hr { border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); margin: 2rem 0; }
    .ask-prose table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 13px; margin: 1rem 0; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
    .ask-prose th { text-align: left; padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; font-weight: 500; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; color: var(--color-muted); background: var(--color-surface); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
    .ask-prose td { padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 5%, transparent); }
    .ask-stream-body {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.95;
      color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 78%, transparent);
      white-space: pre-wrap;
      word-break: break-word;
    }

    #ask-messages .ask-msg-user {
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    #ask-messages .ask-msg-user .ask-msg-label {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 10px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      color: var(--color-muted);
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    #ask-messages .ask-msg-user .ask-msg-text {
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: 15px;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--color-fg);
      background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 6%, transparent);
      padding: 0.85rem 1.1rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }

    #ask-messages .ask-msg-ai {
      padding-bottom: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-fg) 8%, transparent);
    }
    #ask-messages .ask-msg-ai .ask-msg-label {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 10px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      color: var(--color-muted);
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: row;
